<td width="263"> <p style="line-height: 1.3em; color: #00253e; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 0; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><strong><a href="https://blogs.gartner.com/robert-hetu/amazon-dash-marketing-genius/" style="color: #00253e;">Amazon Dash was marketing genius</a> (Gartner Blog Network): </strong>Basically, the argument goes that Amazon forced other retailers to get innovative, and the ones that followed its lead are thriving. <br><br><strong><a href="https://blogs.gartner.com/robert-hetu/walmart-empire-strikes-back-unified-retail-commerce/" style="color: #00253e;">Walmart, the empire strikes back through unified retail commerce</a> (Gartner Blog Network): </strong> “Unified retail commerce first involves understanding how customers use technology in their everyday lives, then deploying technology that makes their lives simpler, better, easier and safer.”</p> </td> 
